## 5. Study Design

- **Design type:** Retrospective new-user cohort
- **Observation type:** Associational; no causal inference is claimed
- **Population:** Synthetic adult patients with type 2 diabetes initiating a GLP-1 receptor agonist
- **Setting:** Synthea-generated EHR records (not claims data)

---

## 6. Index Date

The index date is the **first observed GLP-1 receptor agonist medication start date**
for each eligible patient. Only the first initiation within the observation period
is used as the index event.

---

## 7. Inclusion and Exclusion Criteria

**Inclusion criteria (all must be met):**

1. Age ≥ {{ config.get('min_age_at_index', 18) }} years on the index date
2. Evidence of type 2 diabetes on or before the index date
3. ≥ {{ config.get('min_baseline_history_days', 365) }} days of observable history before the index date
4. ≥ {{ config.get('min_follow_up_days', 180) }} days of observable follow-up after the index date (or until death)
5. First GLP-1 initiation within the observation period

**Exclusion criteria applied:**

{% if config.get('exclude_type1_diabetes') %}- Type 1 diabetes (any record on or before index date)
{% endif %}{% if config.get('exclude_gestational_diabetes') %}- Gestational diabetes (any record on or before index date)
{% endif %}{% if config.get('exclude_pregnancy_at_index') %}- Pregnancy overlapping the index date (±30-day window)
{% endif %}{% if config.get('exclude_missing_demographics') %}- Missing required demographics
{% endif %}

---

## 8. Baseline and Follow-Up Windows

| Window | Duration | Notes |
