| Baseline | {{ config.get('baseline_days', 365) }} days before index | Strictly < index date; no look-ahead |
| Follow-up | {{ config.get('follow_up_days', 180) }} days after index | Censored at death or last encounter if earlier |

---

## 9. Exposure Definition

**Exposure class:** GLP-1 receptor agonist (text-based concept matching)

**Concept set members searched:**

- semaglutide
- liraglutide
- dulaglutide
- exenatide
- tirzepatide

Matching is case-insensitive substring search against Synthea medication
description fields. This approach is not equivalent to validated phenotyping
with an official vocabulary.

---

## 10. Outcome Definition

**Primary outcome:** Any emergency department (ED) encounter during the
{{ config.get('follow_up_days', 180) }}-day follow-up window.

ED encounters are identified by `encounter_class = 'emergency'` in the
standardized encounters table. This classification is derived from Synthea's
simulation model and does not correspond to a validated CMS site-of-service
definition.

**Secondary outcome:** Any inpatient encounter during the follow-up window.

---

## 11. Covariates

Baseline covariates are derived from data strictly **before** the index date
(no look-ahead):

| Covariate | Type | Source |
|-----------|------|--------|
| Age at index (years) | Continuous | Birth date + index date |
| Age group (18-34, 35-49, 50-64, 65-74, 75+) | Categorical | Derived |
| Sex | Categorical | standardized.patients |
| Race | Categorical | standardized.patients |
| Ethnicity | Categorical | standardized.patients |
| GLP-1 drug initiated | Categorical | standardized.medications |
| Baseline ED encounter count | Continuous | 365-day lookback |
| Baseline inpatient encounter count | Continuous | 365-day lookback |
| Baseline outpatient encounter count | Continuous | 365-day lookback |
| Number of distinct conditions | Continuous | Ever on/before index |
| Number of active medications | Continuous | Baseline window |
| Hypertension (yes/no) | Binary | SNOMED text match |
| Chronic kidney disease (yes/no) | Binary | SNOMED text match |
| Cardiovascular disease (yes/no) | Binary | SNOMED text match |
| Latest HbA1c (%) | Continuous | Baseline window; may be missing |
| Latest BMI (kg/m²) | Continuous | Baseline window; may be missing |

